			<ns0:name>pho...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/117980525918552686609/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The original design of SelLdrLauncher{Base, Standalone} class assumed there will be a single instance which will have a single owner and the class itself manages all its resource. However, with the introduction of process support, this assumption is no longer valid as we might have multiple instances, e.g. the command channel might be shared by multiple processes. This requires keeping around multiple instances of SelLdrLauncher and it would be therefore useful to make them reference countable to allow automatic reference management.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-09-27T23:32:14.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-09-27T18:48:35.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>Make SelLdrLauncher{Base, Standalone} reference countable</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Enhancement</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-TCB</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3050/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3050" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/3050" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>1</ns2:stars><ns2:id>3050</ns2:id></ns0:entry>